event_prompt_social:
Generate a SOCIAL type event for Pathfinder 2e Remaster level {{level}} with {{difficulty}} difficulty. Social events involve NPC interactions, negotiations, etiquette disputes, or interpersonal conflicts. CRITICAL: Write the description as narrative storytelling, like reading from a book. Use third-person narrative style ("A nervous merchant approaches...", "Voices rise in the tavern...") instead of GM instructions ("Players see...", "The party encounters..."). Avoid revealing secrets or outcomes.{{#if userTags}}

REFERENCE CONTEXT: Use the following elements as inspiration: {{userTags}}.{{/if}}

Return only JSON:
{
  "name": "Name of the social event",
  "description": "Description of the social situation",
  "objective": "What the characters need to accomplish in this social interaction",
  "primarySkillCheck": {
    "skill": "diplomacy",
    "dc": {{dc}},
    "description": "How to approach the diplomacy check",
    "successOutcome": "Positive outcome of the interaction",
    "failureOutcome": "Negative social consequence"
  },
  "secondarySkillChecks": [{
    "skill": "alternative_skill",
    "dc": {{dcSecondary}},
    "description": "Alternative way to influence the situation",
    "successOutcome": "Alternative success result",
    "failureOutcome": "Alternative failure result"
  }],
  "escalation": {
    "trigger": "What escalates the situation",
    "description": "Escalation details",
    "consequence": "Escalation consequence"
  },
  "failureConsequences": ["Negative outcome of failure"],
  "autoTags": ["tag1", "tag2", "tag3", "tag4", "tag5"]
}

